sudo yum update -y


Install docker on Linux 2
sudo amazon-linux-extras install docker




Start docker service
sudo service docker start




Add the ec2-user to the docker group so you can execute Docker commands without using sudo.
sudo usermod -a -G docker ec2-user




Refresh and run docker without sudo. Get docker info and version
docker info
docker --version




Run the official AWS CLI version 2 Docker image
docker run --rm -it amazon/aws-cli command




Pull Mirth Image
docker pull nextgenhealthcare/connect:latest



Run mirth Image on EC2 server on port 8080/8443 without storing it in a repo
docker run -d -p 8080:8080 nextgenhealthcare/connect:latest
docker run -d -p 8443:8443 nextgenhealthcare/connect:latest
